						"title": "The path to VPN replacement ",
						"subtitle": "Why and how to move faster toward modern secure remote access",
						"copy": "Many organizations recognize the need for VPN alternatives in order to keep up with growing demand for fast, secure, and resilient internal access. As a result, 74% of organizations have — or plan to — replace their VPN with Zero Trust Network Access (ZTNA).\n\nThe path to VPN replacement offers concrete guidance for security and connectivity teams (which can span IT, networking, engineering, and infrastructure roles) to:\n\n- __Build__ the business case for modernizing secure remote access now\n- __Align__ project ownership and implementation across IT and security stakeholders \n- __Plan__ for a phased ZTNA rollout (with example approaches from other organizations)\n- __Assess__ vendors, with 10 sample questions to help evaluate underlying technology\n\nLearn how to accelerate buy-in and kickstart your VPN migration journey now.\n<br><br>\n\n![VPN whitepaper cover image](//cf-assets.www.cloudflare.com/slt3lc6tev37/owxGx4HU37XvgxeWMkDJX/af382b1856663ed98ccb812d67e436cb/VPN-whitepaper-cover-image.png)",
